Sentencas: It is shown that the electrochemical resistance of mixed conducting solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) model cathodes can be reduced drastically by a short but strong dc polarization of the cell.
Titulo: Strong performance improvement of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δSOFC cathodes by electrochemical activation

Sentencas: The samples investigated are dense thin-film microelectrodes of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta on a yttria-stabilized zirconia solid electrolyte.
Titulo: Strong performance improvement of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δSOFC cathodes by electrochemical activation

Sentencas: Relative performance improvements of more than two orders of magnitude can be achieved with a cathodic dc bias of the order of 1 V, applied for a few minutes at fuel cell operating temperature.
Titulo: Strong performance improvement of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δSOFC cathodes by electrochemical activation

Sentencas: The positive effect on the electrode performance corresponds to an acceleration of the oxygen surface exchange reaction, initially the resistance determining process.
Titulo: Strong performance improvement of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δSOFC cathodes by electrochemical activation

Sentencas: For this surface-related resistance, absolute values as low as 0.065 Omega cm(2) at 700 S C have been obtained.
Titulo: Strong performance improvement of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δSOFC cathodes by electrochemical activation

Sentencas: After such an activation, the resistance slowly increases again on a much larger time scale, indicating the possibility of a steady performance enhancement by a periodic activation with short dc pulses.
Titulo: Strong performance improvement of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δSOFC cathodes by electrochemical activation

Sentencas: X-ray photoelectron spectra show that a strong cathodic polarization severely changes the cation concentrations within the outermost surface layer of the electrode, and these field-induced surface compositional changes are assumed to be the main cause of the performance improvement.
Titulo: Strong performance improvement of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δSOFC cathodes by electrochemical activation
